Build step 2 of the local agent system: add a Signal transport.

Requirements:
- Keep the current TypeScript local-agent core and reuse the existing Main Agent and Meta Agent flow.
- Integrate Signal via `signal-cli-rest-api` as the transport layer.
- Support receiving messages from Signal and sending replies back to Signal.
- Add a transport mode switch so the app can run in:
  - CLI mode
  - Signal mode
- In Signal mode, keep printing the conversation to stdout for observability (step 2b).
- Restrict Signal access to exactly one allowed user/phone number in this step.
- Reject or ignore messages from any other Signal sender.
- Keep session handling per Signal conversation/user.
- After every accepted Signal message:
  - run Main Agent
  - persist a trace
  - run Meta Agent
  - save a proposed config patch
- Keep the architecture modular so Telegram or web transports can be added later.
- Add clear config for:
  - Signal REST base URL
  - local agent Signal number
  - allowed remote Signal user number
  - mode selection
- Do not expose a public multi-user design yet; single-user only in this step.
- Include strong typing, clean architecture, and comments.
